---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL; // e.g. "/emoria/"

const grounding = [
  { t: 'Ten years in the room', d: 'Integration daycare centres, residential youth care, intensive-support groups, special-needs and welcome schools, and family counselling — with a particular focus on families with and without a refugee or migration background.' },
  { t: 'A deliberate path', d: 'Years first with children aged two to seven in early-years education, then into youth work and youth welfare — which sharpened one conviction: the earlier children learn to notice and express feelings, the more stably they develop.' },
  { t: 'Grounded in the research', d: 'The method draws on developmental psychology, Vygotsky, Goleman’s emotional intelligence, and current Social-Emotional Learning research — so it holds up for professional educational settings.' },
];
---

<Base title="About Cemil — EMORIA" current="About"
  description="EMORIA was built by Cemil Can Özkaya, a Berlin social pedagogue, over ten years of working with children and families.">
  <article class="bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-14 pt-36 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[var(--color-brand)]">✦ About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl sm:text-6xl">Cemil Can Özkaya</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        State-recognised social pedagogue and educator · Berlin
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-6 px-6 pb-16 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
      <p>
        EMORIA didn’t start as a product. It started as a question I couldn’t put down
        after years of working with children, young people and families: <span class="italic">how can children
        be supported, early on, to understand their feelings, express them, and talk about
        them with others?</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        Again and again I saw the same thing — many conflicts, misunderstandings and
        struggles came down to one ability: being able to express a feeling, a need, a
        boundary. And I saw how rarely children get a safe place to practise it. Many
        families simply don’t have the tools to talk with their children about feelings —
        not for lack of love, but for lack of support.
      </p>
      <p>
        So instead of working through the same cycle with one child at a time, I set out to
        build something with broader reach — a method parents, educators and therapists
        could all draw on. EMORIA is the result of that practice, and of a deep conviction
        that emotional literacy is one of the most important foundations a child can have.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream-deep)]">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
        <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
          {grounding.map((g) => (
            <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-card)] bg-white/60 p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl">{g.t}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">{g.d}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl text-center text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          Cemil speaks four languages, plays seven instruments, and has built deep trust with
          children, families and colleagues across every setting he’s worked in. That
          practice is the foundation EMORIA is built on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 text-center">
      <img src={`${base}img/yubuu-cutout.png`} alt="Yubuu" class="mx-auto mb-4 h-28 w-auto drop-shadow-[0_14px_20px_rgba(43,42,40,0.16)]" />
      <h2 class="text-3xl">Bring EMORIA to your Kita</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        If your kindergarten or practice would like to be among the first to try EMORIA,
        Cemil would be glad to talk.
      </p>
      <a href={`${base}contact`} class="mt-7 inline-block rounded-[var(--radius-pill)] bg-[var(--color-brand)] px-8 py-3.5 font-[var(--font-body)] font-semibold text-white shadow-[var(--shadow-soft)] transition hover:bg-[var(--color-brand-deep)]">
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
